  <prompt>
    Add dispatch of `memory.promotion_resolved` from `MatterMemoryPromotionService.ApproveAsync` AND `RejectAsync` (after the Cosmos status-update succeeds), plus `memory.fact_promoted` from `ApproveAsync` only (after the durable T3 `IMatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` write succeeds), per architecture Â§6.4 + ADR-030 v2 amendment + spec FR-32. Also emit `context.decision_made { decision: "promotion_approved" | "promotion_rejected" }` for T6 audit per architecture Â§6.4. Payload shapes match architecture Â§6.4 verbatim; ADR-015 tier-1 safe (no fact content beyond the original 80-char `factSummary` preview if echoed).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in PaneEventBus dispatch + ADR-015 tier-1 audit + ADR-030 v2 memory channel semantics.</role>

  <goal>
    `MatterMemoryPromotionService.ApproveAsync` emits TWO events on success: `memory.fact_promoted { factId, matterId, source }` (after `AppendFactAsync` succeeds) and `memory.promotion_resolved { promotionId, decision: 'approved', factId }` (after status update succeeds). Both emit `context.decision_made` for T6 audit. `RejectAsync` emits ONE event: `memory.promotion_resolved { promotionId, decision: 'rejected' }` (no `fact_promoted`); also emits `context.decision_made`. Unit tests cover all four emission sites + ordering invariants (e.g., `fact_promoted` emitted only AFTER `AppendFactAsync` returns success). Parallel-safe with task 096 â€” different dispatch sites (Queue vs Approve/Reject).
  </goal>

  <context>
